In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims April 2017 as National Donate Life Month in the United States. He acknowledges the generosity of organ and tissue donors who save lives and recognizes the achievements of healthcare and science professionals involved in transplants. Despite an increase in transplants performed in 2016, there is still a need for more donors as over 118,000 people are currently waiting for organ transplants. President Trump encourages Americans to become organ and tissue donors and highlights the fact that one organ donor can save up to eight lives, while one tissue donor can help 75 people heal. He calls upon various groups and organizations to raise awareness about the urgent need for donors throughout the country.